<DIV id="nstext" valign="bottom">
<H3>AuraCriticalSection_Create</H3>
<p>
        	Creates shared memory.
        </p>
<div class="proto">
<TABLE cellspacing="3" cellpadding="2" style="font-size:90%">
<TR valign="top">
<TD colspan="4" class="datatype">AURA_API AuraCriticalSection_Create(
        </TD>
</TR>
<TR valign="top">
<TD width="8%"></TD>
<TD class="datatype">WString</TD>
<TD class="param">name<span style="color:black; font-size:110%">,</span></TD>
</TR>
<TR valign="top">
<TD width="8%"></TD>
<TD class="datatype">MemorySize</TD>
<TD class="param">size<span style="color:black; font-size:110%">,</span></TD>
</TR>
<TR valign="top">
<TD width="8%"></TD>
<TD class="datatype">Boolean</TD>
<TD class="param">commit<span style="color:black; font-size:110%">,</span></TD>
</TR>
<TR valign="top">
<TD width="8%"></TD>
<TD class="datatype">ISharedMemory **</TD>
<TD class="param">ppSharedMemory<span style="color:black; font-size:110%">,</span></TD>
</TR>
<TR valign="top">
<TD width="8%"></TD>
<TD class="datatype">Boolean *</TD>
<TD class="param">pAlreadyExists</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD colspan="5" class="datatype">);</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</div>
<br />
<H4>Parameters</H4>
<DL><DT class="param" style="color:#222222;margin-left:42">name</DT>
<DD style="margin-left:80"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:black">
                    	[in] The object name of the shared memory
                    <BR /><BR />
</font></DD>
<DT class="param" style="color:#222222;margin-left:42">size</DT>
<DD style="margin-left:80"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:black">
                    	[in] Specifies the size of the shared memory block
                    <BR /><BR />
</font></DD>
<DT class="param" style="color:#222222;margin-left:42">commit</DT>
<DD style="margin-left:80"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:black">
                    	[in] Specifies whether to allocate all the physical memory of the shared memory upon 
                    	creation.
                    <BR /><BR />
</font></DD>
<DT class="param" style="color:#222222;margin-left:42">ppSharedMemory</DT>
<DD style="margin-left:80"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:black">
                    	[out] Interface pointer to the shared memory object, if the function succeeds.
					<BR /><BR />
</font></DD>
<DT class="param" style="color:#222222;margin-left:42">pAlreadyExists</DT>
<DD style="margin-left:80"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:black">
                    	[out] Used to acquire whether the specified SharedMemory object already existed, Ignore the parameter if it is null
					<BR /><BR />
</font></DD>
</DL>
<h4>Return Value</h4>
<p><table class="agility_table" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<THEAD class="head"><TD class="cell">Return value</TD>
<TD class="cell">Description</TD>
</THEAD>
<TR><TD class="cell">NOERROR</TD>
<TD class="cell">Function succeeds in creating a named event object</TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD class="cell">E_INVALID_ARGUMENT</TD>
<TD class="cell">Invalid argument(s)</TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD class="cell">E_SERVICE_NAME_TOO_LONG</TD>
<TD class="cell">The service name is beyond the confines (256 characters)</TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD class="cell">E_ALREADY_EXIST</TD>
<TD class="cell">A non-SharedMemory  object  already existed ,whose name is the same as the Event one</TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD class="cell">E_OUT_OF_MEMORY</TD>
<TD class="cell">Insufficient memory</TD>
</TR>
</table></p>
<h4>Remarks</h4>
<p>
    		esName can not be null, and also cant be the same name as other named service object in system,
    		if so, return E_ALREADY_EXISTS.
    	</p>
<p><i>ppSharedMemory</i>
 can be set as null when this process does not operate on this shared memory£»Release must 
        	be called to release this pointer after user operate on this shared memory by <i>ppSharedMemory</i>
.
        </p>
<p>
    		Other process can access and use this object through the name specified by <i>esName</i>
 and by EzFindService</a> function.
    	 </p>
